ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would highly recommend this course to other graduate students who want to get a basic understanding of nanomaterials and their synthesis
Highly recommend even if it is not your field of study. In many cases this material can be applied to other fields and the skills gained in literature reviewing is definitely applicable

I would highly recommend this class to anyone working with nanoscale materials. The discussion of characterization methods was particularly useful since several methods were discussed that I had not encountered before.
If students were interested in the Nanomaterial synsthesis, the course would be helpful
I would recommend this course to anyone who is working in or intends to work in the field of nanosynthesis (even more if someone is working with carbon).

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Highly applicable to my research. Broad understanding of nanomaterial field. Critical skills for paper finding/reading/writing. I work in nanomaterials; this class was critical to me.
I'm becoming more familar with the nano material reserach, and also have opportunities to be exposed to the recent research direction.
